The paper deals with visual object tracking using deep learning techniques, specifically recurrent convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) for regression in the temporal domain, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach for object tracking, which involves the use of region information, and this falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with video tracking datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the computational cost of the proposed method, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
